Welcome to KansasMoney.gov!

Kansas consumers' one-stop shop for financial education.

Click here and find out what we're about!

Get Smart About Money

Free online courses. At your own pace. On your own time.

Learn more here!

Who sponsors KansasMoney?

A collaborative group of Kansas state agencies are here to serve you and encourage your financial success.

Learn more here!

File a Complaint

Need to file a complaint but not sure where to turn?

Click here to get started!

Stay in the Game!

Learning to manage and protect your finances can enable you to maintain the freedom and lifestyle you want.
NBC World Series fans: follow us @KansasMoney on Facebook.

Learn more here!

New on Kansas Money:

You CAN Invest in Stocks, Even on a Modest Budget

Many people believe you should have a substantial income or savings to purchase stock listed on major exchanges. Nothing could be further from the truth.

Debt Management: Foundational to Financial Success

Tracking your expenses and keeping debt manageable are essential to building personal wealth.

Elder Investment Fraud

Seniors are the number one target of con-artists. Learn how to protect yourself and avoid becoming a victim of investment fraud.

Smart About Money

Free online courses. At your own pace. On your own time.

The Essential Guide to Finances for Veterans and Military Members

There are many benefits, special programs, and tax breaks that apply only to military members. 

Speakers Bureau

Request a speaker from one of the KansasMoney.gov agencies today!

I have a question about…

KansasMoney.gov is the site for financial information concerning Kansans.

Kansas State agencies have cooperated to bring you a one-stop shop financial education website. Our goal is to inform you about how to manage and protect your money.

Here's what you'll find on KansasMoney.gov

Manage $

Manage Your Money

Includes Save, Invest, Taxes, Borrowing Money, Debt, Retirement 101, and Unclaimed Property

Protect $

Protect Your Loved Ones and Your $ from Life's Dangers

Includes Fraud and Insurance

KansasMoney.gov Partners

KansasMoney.gov is a collaborative effort from these state agencies that unifies and simplifies the consumer information available from the State of Kansas.

Includes Kansas Department of Revenue, Kansas State Treasurer’s Office, Attorney General’s Office, State Bank Commissioner of Kansas, Kansas Department of Credit Unions, Kansas Securities Commissioner, Kansas Insurance Department, Speakers Bureau, and File a Complaint

Education

Financial Literacy Organizations and Tools

Includes Events, Smart About Money, Resources, Calculators, Quizzes, and Infographics

Recent News from KansasMoney.gov

Kansas Securities Commissioner Now Accepting Educational Grant Applications from Organizations

Organizations focused on financial education should apply for a grant from the Office of the Kansas Securities Commissioner Read more…

From the Kansas Office of the Attorney General - Pennsylvania Man Pleads Guilty to Financial Crimes

A Pennsylvania man yesterday pleaded guilty to four felony counts of a sale of an unregistered security, Kansas Attorney General Derek Schmidt said. Read more…
